10 Section 1. Section 61-8-806, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "61-8-806. Blood, and breath, and oral fluid tests of commercial vehicle operators -- procedure
12 -- suspension. (1) A person who operates a commercial motor vehicle upon the ways of this state open to the
13 public is considered to have given consent to one or more tests of the person's blood, or breath, or oral fluid for
14 the purpose of determining a measured amount or detected presence of alcohol in the person's body if the
15 person is requested to submit to the test or tests by a peace officer who has reasonable grounds to believe that
16 the person was driving or in actual physical control of a commercial motor vehicle upon the ways of this state
17 open to the public while having a measured alcohol concentration or detected presence of alcohol. The peace
18 officer may designate the blood, or breath, or oral fluid test or tests to be administered and may request that the
19 person submit to a preliminary alcohol screening test before a blood, breath, oral fluid, or urine test is taken.
20 (2) A person who is unconscious or who is otherwise incapable of refusal is considered not to have
21 withdrawn the consent provided in subsection (1).
22 (3) If a person refuses to submit to one or more tests designated by the officer, the test or tests
23 may not be given, but the officer shall immediately seize the person's commercial driver's license and forward
24 the license to the department, along with a report certified under penalty of law that the officer had reasonable
25 grounds to believe that the person was driving or was in actual physical control of a commercial motor vehicle
26 upon ways of this state open to the public while having a measurable alcohol concentration or detected
27 presence of alcohol and that the person had refused to submit to one or more tests upon the request of the
28 officer. Upon receipt of the report, the department shall suspend the license for a period provided in subsection
